history.content:
I took 170 and 126 last semester, I got As in both, and found it more than manageable. Just don't fall behind on lecture and practice a lot of the material in 126 and you should be good. 

--

I also took 170 and 126 and got As on both this semester. I don't think "more than manageable" is accurate, the pset load is really heavy (each is 10+ hrs, weekly, not to mention labs for 126 and both have projects at the end). 162 and 126 might be really hard to keep up with as workload will be very intense.
I took 170 and 126 last semester, I got As in both, and found it more than manageable. Just don't fall behind on lecture and practice a lot of the material in 126 and you should be good.

children.subject: As a word of caution, depending on where your skills/comfort levels are, 162 might be significantly more work than 170 in terms of difficulty/time commitment.

i took both 170 and 126 this semester, and while I was able to do well in both I wish I had more time for myself throughout the semester so I personally wouldn't recommend if you have a reasonable way to get around having to take both at once
